 Among all the posts I have read here, there are but a scarce few of you that I would want defending My freedom.  ..the true conflict here is not Whether to fight for freedom or not, but Why (and therefore, When) one fights for freedom.<br>
<br>
For you people that 'think' that this great country was founded based on 'selfless service and sacrifice for the sake of others:'<br>
<br>
I suggest you Think again.  They fought for themselves...and the freedom of the rest was a concern, but NOT the prime justification.  These men committed treason.  It was not to be taken lightly.  They knew it and did it anyway, because they, themselves, were not willing to sacrifice their <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> own</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> lives as a means to the ends of others. ...and I for one am glad, grateful and solemnly proud of their choice of battles.  But it only means something to me because they didn't have to do it, they chose to.  They did not do it for me and I don't delude myself into pretending they did--nor would I want them to!!!!  Patrick Henry did <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> not</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> say &quot;Give them liberty or give me death&quot;  ... he said &quot;...I know not what course others may take; but as for me, give me liberty or give me death!&quot;<br>
<br>
They also used the best technology available to them at the time.  <br>
<br>
Glade, we <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> do</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> know where the terrorists are; we've known for a long time which countries make a practice of harboring terrorists and condoning terrorism against freedom.  'We have the technology' -let us now use it.  We should bomb every man, woman, child and animal in those countries.  I don't know about the rest of you, but that woman (on the west bank celebrations) on TV saying how she wished all of her children would grow up to be that brave told me exactly how deep their hatred of us (representatives of freedom) runs and how well we need to exterminate them, their families, their children and those that hide and or protect them ...even those who don't openly agree with them yet actively hide them.  But a 'prolonged military campaign' is <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> not</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> the answer.  ..it smells strongly of propaganda, and yes it will cost many unnecessary American (and potentially ally) causualties of war.  4,700+ is more than enough Americans dead already. This BS can be taken care of once and for all.  'We have the technology'<br>
<br>
Triff's post advocates nothing more (and nothing less!!) than rational self-interest, as our founding fathers also advocated.  Their commitment was to the principle of <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> individual</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> rights, and of fighting off the yoke of tyrants.  Triff hasn't said he wouldn't fight; he's said he doesn't recognize your (or anyone's) 'right' to sacrifice him for their (your or your child's) sake.  The winning team will be made of such people, a team of individuals; each fighting for his own rights, freedom and life.  Americans.<br>
<br>
Here's an Ayn Rand quote for ya:<br>
&quot;What most people are evading today is the realization that under the lip service they are paying to an anti-totalitarian crusade, they have accepted all the basic premises of a totalitarian philosophy.&quot;<br>
<br>
How ironic that those throwing the word 'coward' around so much are themselves the moral cowards.<br>
<br>
